01:17:44,527 --> 01:17:46,460
We'll get killed.

1010
01:17:46,529 --> 01:17:50,630
Damn. I should
have said 2:30.
Oh, what's the difference?

1011
01:17:50,699 --> 01:17:53,200
At least
they gave US 24.

1012
01:17:53,269 --> 01:17:55,936
Ow!

1013
01:17:56,004 --> 01:17:59,973
Ooh!
It's my brother.
He's been shot.

1014
01:18:00,042 --> 01:18:02,642
My leg!
My poor little brother.

1015
01:18:02,711 --> 01:18:04,911
Oh, god!
My poor little brother.

1016
01:18:04,980 --> 01:18:09,483
What happened, Clayton?
He was biting off
a chaw of tobacco when...

1017
01:18:09,552 --> 01:18:12,486
- Yeah?
- I shot him.

1018
01:18:12,555 --> 01:18:14,488
Excuse me?

1019
01:18:14,557 --> 01:18:17,791
- It was my tobacco.
- That's a good reason.

1020
01:18:17,859 --> 01:18:21,395
Anybody here know
how to remove a bullet?
Honey?

1021
01:18:21,464 --> 01:18:25,665
- Phil?
- I can't pick up a scalpel.

1022
01:18:25,734 --> 01:18:28,868
- How bad is it?
- Only a flesh wound.

1023
01:18:28,937 --> 01:18:30,971
Oh.

1024
01:18:31,039 --> 01:18:34,774
Aren't you going to
help Mr. Ferguson,
daddy?

1025
01:18:43,486 --> 01:18:46,153
- Come on. Move him.
- Easy.

1026
01:18:46,222 --> 01:18:48,955
Bring him over
into my wagon.

1027
01:18:49,024 --> 01:18:51,925
We'll need hot water
and plenty of towels.

1028
01:18:51,994 --> 01:18:54,661
I was just dropping--

1029
01:18:54,730 --> 01:18:56,663
You done shot me!

1030
01:18:56,732 --> 01:19:01,435
Aah!
what are you doing, doc?

1031
01:19:01,504 --> 01:19:04,438
- Scalpel.
- Scalpel. Mm-hmm.

1032
01:19:04,507 --> 01:19:06,440
Here you are.

1033
01:19:06,509 --> 01:19:10,277
Aah!

1034
01:19:10,346 --> 01:19:12,946
Aah!

1035
01:19:13,015 --> 01:19:15,449
Scissors.

1036
01:19:15,518 --> 01:19:17,451
Scissors.

1037
01:19:17,520 --> 01:19:21,288
Aah!
woo!

1038
01:19:24,527 --> 01:19:26,960
What's the matter
with you?

1039
01:19:39,542 --> 01:19:41,808
I did it.

1040
01:19:41,877 --> 01:19:45,412
I got in there,
and I forgot
about all my fears.

1041
01:19:45,481 --> 01:19:49,583
It was like old times.
The knife became
an extension of my hand.

1042
01:19:49,652 --> 01:19:52,852
The blood, the tissue--
none of it bothered me.

1043
01:19:52,921 --> 01:19:55,355
Dr. Taylor,
I'm proud of you.

1044
01:19:55,424 --> 01:19:58,192
Oh. Oh.

1045
01:19:58,260 --> 01:20:00,494
Uh,
so my brother,

1046
01:20:00,563 --> 01:20:03,129
he can walk
again?

1047
01:20:05,067 --> 01:20:09,002
Oh, uh...
About that, Clay,
you know,

1048
01:20:09,071 --> 01:20:12,005
these flesh wounds
can be pretty tricky.

1049
01:20:12,074 --> 01:20:15,509
There are
complications and--
you had to amputate?

1050
01:20:15,578 --> 01:20:18,011
No, no, no,
no, no, no.

1051
01:20:18,080 --> 01:20:21,515
The leg is, uh, fine.
A little stiff.

1052
01:20:21,584 --> 01:20:23,517
Now, that's
to be expected.

1053
01:20:25,254 --> 01:20:29,022
Well, you know,
actually, Clay, uh...

1054
01:20:29,091 --> 01:20:32,526
The leg is not
the only part that's stiff.

1055
01:20:32,595 --> 01:20:35,529
Actually, his whole body
is kind of, uh--

1056
01:20:35,598 --> 01:20:38,232
well, he's, uh...
He's, uh...

1057
01:20:39,401 --> 01:20:41,335
He's dead.

1058
01:20:41,403 --> 01:20:45,472
But he, uh,
he wanted you
to have this, huh?

1059
01:20:46,575 --> 01:20:49,109
Oh! My tobacco!

1060
01:20:49,177 --> 01:20:51,278
Thanks, doc.

1061
01:20:54,883 --> 01:20:58,084
Uh... oh...

1062
01:20:58,153 --> 01:21:01,622
Harlow!
Harlow!

1063
01:21:02,625 --> 01:21:04,558
Harlow!

1064
01:21:04,627 --> 01:21:08,061
Harlow... uh!

1065
01:21:08,130 --> 01:21:10,063
Sorry, sir.
You were delirious.

1066
01:21:10,132 --> 01:21:12,566
You want to
slap me back?

1067
01:21:12,635 --> 01:21:14,568
You're more
than welcome to.

1068
01:21:14,637 --> 01:21:17,571
Lieutenant.
Yes, sir.

1069
01:21:17,640 --> 01:21:20,574
I was dreaming.
Yes, you were.

1070
01:21:20,643 --> 01:21:24,077
Did I say anything?
Well, you, uh,
mentioned Harlow.

1071
01:21:24,146 --> 01:21:26,880
Harlow!
You two have some sort
of history together?

1072
01:21:26,948 --> 01:21:31,117
No!
Yes, yes, yes.

1073
01:21:31,186 --> 01:21:33,119
Yes, we do.

1074
01:21:33,188 --> 01:21:35,989
It was about 20 years ago...

1075
01:21:36,057 --> 01:21:38,992
When Harlow
led the donner party,

1076
01:21:39,060 --> 01:21:42,496
and I, rightfully so,
appropriated many
of his horses...

1077
01:21:42,564 --> 01:21:47,100
And most of his supplies
for my raid on the Mexicans.

1078
01:21:47,169 --> 01:21:51,638
While his pathetic attempts
at rescue failed, of course,

1079
01:21:51,707 --> 01:21:55,141
I rode on to glory
and became a colonel.

1080
01:21:55,210 --> 01:21:59,513
They others froze
and ate each other.
Oh, gee!

1081
01:21:59,581 --> 01:22:01,515
Luck of the draw,
lieutenant.

1082
01:22:01,583 --> 01:22:04,017
Just the luck
of the draw.

1083
01:22:05,921 --> 01:22:07,854
Ooh!

1084
01:22:07,923 --> 01:22:10,857
But this is just
the kind of thing...

1085
01:22:10,926 --> 01:22:13,860
That the press blows
way out of proportion,

1086
01:22:13,929 --> 01:22:19,032
especially in light
of a presidential campaign.

1087
01:22:19,100 --> 01:22:21,468
It's--
it's official, sir?

1088
01:22:21,537 --> 01:22:24,538
Yes, lieutenant.

1089
01:22:24,606 --> 01:22:27,541
It's official.

1090
01:22:27,609 --> 01:22:29,543
Damn that Harlow.

1091
01:22:29,611 --> 01:22:32,546
Thought he drank himself
into oblivion years ago.

1092
01:22:32,614 --> 01:22:36,049
But no matter.
I'll take care
of him tomorrow.

1093
01:22:36,117 --> 01:22:38,051
The secret dies
with him.

1094
01:22:38,119 --> 01:22:40,620
No one else knows.
Except for me.

1095
01:22:40,689 --> 01:22:44,057
Who told you?
You did, sir.

1096
01:22:44,125 --> 01:22:46,893
Very observant,
lieutenant.

1097
01:22:48,296 --> 01:22:50,564
Very observant.

1098
01:22:50,632 --> 01:22:53,567
But now I think
you have two choices--

1099
01:22:53,635 --> 01:22:58,071
use your head and accept
a plum position
in my cabinet...

1100
01:22:58,139 --> 01:23:02,576
Or search for your brains
by the light of a candle.

1101
01:23:02,644 --> 01:23:04,944
Good night,
Mr. President.

1102
01:23:07,983 --> 01:23:09,983
Good night,
Mr. Secretary.

1103
01:23:12,988 --> 01:23:14,921
Are the men in bed?

1104
01:23:14,990 --> 01:23:17,591
Well, they were, sir.
I don't know about now.

1105
01:23:17,659 --> 01:23:21,595
Good. All right,
lieutenant.
Tuck you in, huh?

1106
01:23:21,663 --> 01:23:25,599
Yes, sir.
I think a bedtime story
would be in order.

1107
01:23:25,667 --> 01:23:29,569
All right, sir. Just one.
It's very late, sir.

1108
01:23:29,638 --> 01:23:33,273
Do you want to hear
Indian Joe meets
the talking rock?

1109
01:23:33,341 --> 01:23:37,310
Well, the colonel's favorite
isthe lone pony
on the high plains.

1110
01:23:37,379 --> 01:23:39,379
All right.
Lone pony, it is.

1111
01:23:45,687 --> 01:23:48,622
Hit me.
Dang. This boy
can drink.

1112
01:23:48,690 --> 01:23:51,625
I need a few more
customers like him.

1113
01:23:51,693 --> 01:23:56,129
Say, dusty, you hear
about that wagon train
heading this way?

1114
01:23:56,197 --> 01:23:59,098
Yeah. A bunch of whores,
degenerates, and murderers.

1115
01:23:59,167 --> 01:24:02,468
There's talk about them
massacring settlers
along the trail--

1116
01:24:02,537 --> 01:24:05,706
pillaging and raping
like it's nobody's business.

1117
01:24:05,774 --> 01:24:09,509
They're letting Indians
sleep with their women.

1118
01:24:09,578 --> 01:24:11,912
Well, they're
going to get theirs.

1119
01:24:11,981 --> 01:24:16,683
There's a rumor that
the seventh cavalry's going
to wipe them out.

1120
01:24:16,752 --> 01:24:19,920
They're sending in
their crackerjack
general larchmont...

1121
01:24:19,989 --> 01:24:22,422
To make sure
the job's done.

1122
01:24:22,491 --> 01:24:25,425
Let's have one
for the seventh cavalry!

1123
01:24:25,494 --> 01:24:28,194
To the good general!

1124
01:24:40,509 --> 01:24:42,442
How am I doing?

1125
01:24:42,511 --> 01:24:45,946
Well, they're still
behind you.

1126
01:24:46,015 --> 01:24:49,950
You know the last time
I was on a horse?

1127
01:24:50,019 --> 01:24:52,318
At the carrousel
in St. Louis.

1128
01:24:52,387 --> 01:24:54,420
And I was thrown.

1129
01:24:54,489 --> 01:24:57,190
The cavalry.

1130
01:24:57,259 --> 01:25:00,460
Oh, my god.
Whoa!

1131
01:25:00,529 --> 01:25:02,696
Circle the wagons!

1132
01:25:02,765 --> 01:25:04,965
Git!

1133
01:25:05,034 --> 01:25:08,869
Phil, I got an idea!
Keep those wagons around!

1134
01:25:08,937 --> 01:25:11,705
Hyah!

1135
01:25:11,774 --> 01:25:15,976
Phil, you know how white guys
always circle in their wagons?

1136
01:25:16,045 --> 01:25:20,147
Makes it easier
for the cavalry
to go around.

1137
01:25:20,215 --> 01:25:22,649
Why don't you
square the wagons?

1138
01:25:22,718 --> 01:25:25,986
The cavalry would
have to go in wide circles.

1139
01:25:26,055 --> 01:25:29,056
Square the wagons!
Square the wagons!

1140
01:25:29,124 --> 01:25:32,292
Square the wagons!
Square the wagons,
whities!

1141
01:25:32,360 --> 01:25:34,627
Square the wagons?
I don't get it!

1142
01:25:43,538 --> 01:25:45,072
Billy!

1143
01:25:48,077 --> 01:25:49,509
Billy!

1144
01:25:49,578 --> 01:25:52,012
Miss Lindsey,
get back.

1145
01:25:55,483 --> 01:25:56,917
I got it!

1146
01:25:56,985 --> 01:26:00,420
So this is what
it looks like in here?

1147
01:26:00,488 --> 01:26:03,023
How do they walk
in these things?

1148
01:26:03,092 --> 01:26:04,624
Big snake!

1149
01:26:08,097 --> 01:26:10,530
What are you doing?
It's filthy.

1150
01:26:10,599 --> 01:26:13,867
I'm hiding behind it.
Get over there.

1151
01:26:13,936 --> 01:26:17,838
What do you think
you're doing with that?
Thank you.

1152
01:26:17,906 --> 01:26:21,208
All right!
Everybody stay down!

1153
01:26:21,276 --> 01:26:26,213
Stay down!
wait for my command to fire!

1154
01:26:32,020 --> 01:26:34,320
And remember...

1155
01:26:34,389 --> 01:26:36,322
No matter what happens,

1156
01:26:36,391 --> 01:26:41,461
no one but no one can take away
what this trip has meant to US.

1157
01:26:44,032 --> 01:26:46,532
I did it, honey.

1158
01:26:46,601 --> 01:26:50,003
I got in there
and forgot my fears.

1159
01:26:50,072 --> 01:26:53,306
Dr. Taylor, I am
very proud of you.

1160
01:27:00,548 --> 01:27:03,683
I didn't properly
introduce myself.
The name's Harlow.

1161
01:27:03,752 --> 01:27:05,852
I'll be
your wagon master.

1162
01:27:14,062 --> 01:27:16,997
Julian, would you mind
scrubbing my back?

1163
01:27:17,065 --> 01:27:21,067
Since that bronc threw me,
I can't reach it.

1164
01:27:59,107 --> 01:28:01,141
All right,
lieutenant!

1165
01:28:01,210 --> 01:28:04,644
Let's sound the attack!
I want my big horn.

1166
01:28:04,713 --> 01:28:08,148
Sir, are you sure
we really need
the big horn?

1167
01:28:08,217 --> 01:28:10,150
Of course, you idiot!

1168
01:28:10,219 --> 01:28:14,154
It instills fear in the enemy
and saps their strength...

1169
01:28:14,223 --> 01:28:16,656
And turns their bowels
to jelly.

1170
01:28:16,725 --> 01:28:20,260
Where's my big horn?
Souza!

1171
01:28:20,329 --> 01:28:23,429
Yes, sir!
Sound the charge.

1172
01:28:25,834 --> 01:28:29,369
Let's kill some people!

1173
01:28:31,606 --> 01:28:35,541
- To glory!
- Charge!

1174
01:28:38,513 --> 01:28:41,348
Charge!

1175
01:28:41,416 --> 01:28:45,952
Damn it.
Honey, is that manual
under the seat?

1176
01:28:49,524 --> 01:28:51,892
Go get them,
dad.

1177
01:29:10,379 --> 01:29:12,879
They've squared
the wagons!

1178
01:29:12,948 --> 01:29:15,215
They've what?

1179
01:29:15,284 --> 01:29:19,585
They're not
shooting, lieutenant.
Why aren't they shooting?

1180
01:29:19,654 --> 01:29:23,390
Sir, these people
aren't renegades.
They're just settlers.

1181
01:29:23,458 --> 01:29:27,560
Fool. That's what
they want you to think.

1182
01:29:27,629 --> 01:29:29,896
Ho!
Ho!

1183
01:29:29,965 --> 01:29:32,032
They're women and children.

1184
01:29:32,100 --> 01:29:37,203
They're settlers.
I ain't shooting.

1185
01:29:37,272 --> 01:29:42,008
- Is that Mr. Harlow?
- Where?

1186
01:29:48,483 --> 01:29:51,418
It's Harlow!
It's Harlow!

1187
01:29:51,486 --> 01:29:53,453
Harlow.

1188
01:29:55,057 --> 01:29:57,223
Harlow.

1189
01:30:02,998 --> 01:30:06,666
Let's go.
Hyah! Come on!

1190
01:30:09,271 --> 01:30:11,804
Hyah!

1191
01:30:17,012 --> 01:30:18,278
All right!

1192
01:30:24,019 --> 01:30:27,887
Hope I'm not
too late to join
your little party.

1193
01:30:27,956 --> 01:30:31,858
Let's forget about
the settlers and shoot him.
Fire when ready.

1194
01:30:31,926 --> 01:30:34,461
Easy, boys.
You may get me,

1195
01:30:34,529 --> 01:30:38,431
but I'm going to take
your fearless leader
with me.

1196
01:30:38,500 --> 01:30:40,433
What should
we do, sir?

1197
01:30:40,502 --> 01:30:44,704
Do? Uh... uh...

1198
01:30:44,772 --> 01:30:48,708
Taylor! Smith!
Have your men form
a human shield around me.

1199
01:30:48,776 --> 01:30:52,078
General, sir,
I'm calling you out.

1200
01:30:57,052 --> 01:31:00,453
I've handled tougher men
than you, Harlow.

1201
01:31:00,522 --> 01:31:03,856
Lieutenant, shoot him.

1202
01:31:03,925 --> 01:31:06,659
I'd like to, sir,
but I'm afraid
my hands are tied.

1203
01:31:06,728 --> 01:31:10,163
He's called you out
in front of the men.

1204
01:31:10,232 --> 01:31:12,999
It's a, you know,
western thing.

1205
01:31:13,068 --> 01:31:16,036
A western thing,
you say?

1206
01:31:16,104 --> 01:31:19,572
General, sir,
I'd like to help you
with your dismount.

1207
01:31:19,641 --> 01:31:21,707
Why, thank you, son.

1208
01:31:38,993 --> 01:31:42,429
You pack
a pretty fair punch
there, Harlow.

1209
01:31:43,998 --> 01:31:47,033
Knock one for me!

1210
01:31:47,102 --> 01:31:51,003
Go, Harlow!
Yeah, that's right!
You heard me!

1211
01:31:51,073 --> 01:31:53,339
Fix his wagon,
Harlow.

1212
01:31:53,408 --> 01:31:55,975
- Aah!
- Aah!

1213
01:32:01,183 --> 01:32:03,483
Good jab.

1214
01:32:06,388 --> 01:32:08,321
Back down on the ground.

1215
01:32:08,390 --> 01:32:10,490
Keep your hands up.

1216
01:32:29,578 --> 01:32:32,011
How long
do these things
usually last?

1217
01:32:32,080 --> 01:32:34,013
How would I know?

1218
01:32:34,082 --> 01:32:36,483
I'm getting
kind of hungry.

1219
01:32:36,551 --> 01:32:40,019
Can I go play?
Sure, sweetheart.

1220
01:32:45,360 --> 01:32:47,293
You're losing him,
Harlow!

1221
01:32:47,362 --> 01:32:50,997
Where are you going?

1222
01:32:52,234 --> 01:32:54,634
Good. Stay down.

1223
01:33:04,279 --> 01:33:06,279
Whoops.

1224
01:33:06,348 --> 01:33:08,448
Aah!

1225
01:33:10,519 --> 01:33:12,718
Would you like
a vanilla wafer?

1226
01:33:12,787 --> 01:33:14,854
Here you go.

1227
01:33:16,991 --> 01:33:20,293
- I got it!
- Yes!

1228
01:33:20,362 --> 01:33:23,963
Harder!
Push hard!

1229
01:33:36,044 --> 01:33:37,977
Huh?

1230
01:33:43,051 --> 01:33:45,051
Okay.

1231
01:33:46,854 --> 01:33:48,854
Get up!

1232
01:34:03,071 --> 01:34:05,205
Yay!

1233
01:34:09,010 --> 01:34:10,943
Over here.
Okay, honey!

1234
01:34:11,012 --> 01:34:14,947
Let's go have
some pie!

1235
01:34:16,751 --> 01:34:19,952
Harlow!
Yeah!

1236
01:34:20,021 --> 01:34:23,456
James aloysius Harlow!

1237
01:34:25,694 --> 01:34:27,960
I knew you'd do it,
buddy!

1238
01:34:28,029 --> 01:34:30,730
You have a seat,
you big hero.

1239
01:34:30,798 --> 01:34:36,336
Today, we open the bounties
of our glorious land
to the common man!

1240
01:34:36,404 --> 01:34:38,338
So look to the west,

1241
01:34:38,406 --> 01:34:41,974
for therein lies
your future!

1242
01:34:42,043 --> 01:34:43,976
Wha--?

1243
01:34:45,179 --> 01:34:48,615
Where the humble wagon...

1244
01:34:48,683 --> 01:34:53,319
- What is it?
- Looks like a wagon train.

1245
01:34:53,388 --> 01:34:55,988
But they're heading east.

1246
01:34:56,057 --> 01:34:59,692
They're going
the wrong way!

1247
01:34:59,761 --> 01:35:04,196
That look good?
My hair look white
to you, son?

1248
01:35:04,266 --> 01:35:06,966
Come see me
when you've got
some mink.

1249
01:35:07,034 --> 01:35:11,404
If I get my hands
on that kid
that scalped me...

1250
01:35:11,473 --> 01:35:15,141
Look at this, dad!
Jeremiah,
put that away!

1251
01:35:15,209 --> 01:35:19,011
Showed initiative.
He'll make a fine
officer one day.

1252
01:35:19,080 --> 01:35:23,182
I'm proud
to be scalped
by a boy like that.

1253
01:35:23,251 --> 01:35:27,186
Listen to me!
Pay no heed
to those fools!

1254
01:35:27,255 --> 01:35:30,323
They're dunderheads!
They're going the wrong way!

1255
01:35:30,392 --> 01:35:33,426
You've got
to listen to me!

1256
01:35:33,495 --> 01:35:36,996
Land for the taking!
Your time is now!

1257
01:35:37,064 --> 01:35:39,999
Land rushers,
get ready!

1258
01:35:40,067 --> 01:35:42,168
Not now!

1259
01:35:42,236 --> 01:35:45,204
About time. Ah, well.

1260
01:35:45,273 --> 01:35:48,007
Smedly!

1261
01:35:51,513 --> 01:35:53,513
Aah!

1262
01:36:04,359 --> 01:36:06,459
Oh, yeah!

1263
01:36:06,528 --> 01:36:08,961
Ha ha ha!

1264
01:36:19,040 --> 01:36:22,975
Should we tell them?
Nah. They wouldn't
listen anyway.

1265
01:36:23,044 --> 01:36:24,977
But who knows?

1266
01:36:25,046 --> 01:36:28,481
Maybe it'll
work out for them.

1267
01:36:30,051 --> 01:36:32,017
Ha ha ha!

1268
01:36:32,086 --> 01:36:34,987
Wagons east!

1269
01:36:43,565 --> 01:36:45,998
Harlow.
Evening, gentlemen.

1270
01:36:46,067 --> 01:36:48,033
Evening.

1271
01:36:48,102 --> 01:36:50,536
I'd like
to thank you both...

1272
01:36:50,605 --> 01:36:53,673
For, uh, well,
for believing in me.

1273
01:36:53,742 --> 01:36:56,542
We never doubted you
for a second, Harlow.

1274
01:36:56,611 --> 01:36:59,512
Not once?

1275
01:36:59,581 --> 01:37:03,282
- Honestly?
- Yeah.

1276
01:37:03,351 --> 01:37:05,885
- Oh, the river crossing.
- Yeah.

1277
01:37:05,953 --> 01:37:08,855
And the fork
in the road.

1278
01:37:08,923 --> 01:37:10,857
Oh, yeah.

1279
01:37:10,925 --> 01:37:12,925
The Indian camp.

1280
01:37:12,994 --> 01:37:15,561
Uh-huh.
And that whole thing--

1281
01:37:15,630 --> 01:37:17,563
I got to get going.

1282
01:37:17,632 --> 01:37:22,101
Come on. Please.
Without you, we wouldn't
even be here.

1283
01:37:22,169 --> 01:37:25,104
When I ride into
St. Louis tomorrow,

1284
01:37:25,172 --> 01:37:29,108
I'll be thinking
of James h. Harlow--
wagon master supreme.

1285
01:37:29,176 --> 01:37:31,611
We'll miss riding
with you, Harlow.

1286
01:37:31,679 --> 01:37:35,180
I appreciate that.
I truly do.
You know what?

1287
01:37:35,249 --> 01:37:38,284
I wouldn't mind
seeing you again.

1288
01:37:38,352 --> 01:37:40,420
I'd look forward
to that,

1289
01:37:40,488 --> 01:37:43,923
especially since
I haven't been paid yet.

1290
01:37:43,991 --> 01:37:47,427
We haven't--
let's wait
until St. Louis.

1291
01:37:47,495 --> 01:37:49,629
He could still
get lost.

1292
01:38:00,007 --> 01:38:01,941
Don't you wish
that, uh...

1293
01:38:02,009 --> 01:38:04,944
That this
would never end.

1294
01:38:05,012 --> 01:38:06,946
Yeah.

1295
01:38:07,014 --> 01:38:09,449
Mmm...

1296
01:38:09,517 --> 01:38:13,453
But, I guess it's--

1297
01:38:13,521 --> 01:38:15,955
yeah. I guess.

1298
01:38:16,023 --> 01:38:18,458
It's over. Yeah.

1299
01:38:21,529 --> 01:38:24,964
Unless...
Yeah?

1300
01:38:25,032 --> 01:38:26,966
Nah.
Unless?

1301
01:38:27,034 --> 01:38:29,969
No. I'd be wrong.
No, Harlow.

1302
01:38:30,037 --> 01:38:33,973
I think I know
what you're thinking,

1303
01:38:34,041 --> 01:38:38,177
and it definitely
wouldn't be wrong.

1304
01:38:38,245 --> 01:38:40,980
Really?
You mean...
Yes.

1305
01:38:41,048 --> 01:38:42,782
Yes!

1306
01:38:42,851 --> 01:38:46,986
That we could
go back and start
all over again?

1307
01:38:47,054 --> 01:38:50,523
No. Definitely wrong.

1308
01:38:50,592 --> 01:38:53,993
Or...
Or?

1309
01:38:54,061 --> 01:38:57,497
We can hook up
and go north
to Canada.

1310
01:38:57,565 --> 01:39:01,333
I hear
it's warm there
all year round.

1311
01:39:01,402 --> 01:39:03,435
Oh, Harlow!

1312
01:39:03,505 --> 01:39:06,906
Oh, Harlow!

1313
01:39:09,143 --> 01:39:12,979
Look. A shooting star.

1314
01:39:13,047 --> 01:39:16,582
Quick. Close your eyes
and make a wish.

1315
01:39:19,487 --> 01:39:21,921
Well, what
did you wish for?

1316
01:39:21,990 --> 01:39:26,425
If I tell you,
it won't come true.

1317
01:39:33,701 --> 01:39:37,336
Aah!
quick!

1318
01:39:37,405 --> 01:39:39,972
What was that?
Wow!

1319
01:39:40,040 --> 01:39:42,007
It's Clayton Ferguson.

1320
01:39:42,076 --> 01:39:45,210
Oh, my god!

1321
01:39:45,279 --> 01:39:47,346
Talk about
your bad luck.

1322
01:39:47,415 --> 01:39:51,384
What do you figure
the chances of that are?

1323
01:39:52,887 --> 01:39:54,820
Where are you
headed, Julian?

1324
01:39:54,889 --> 01:39:57,289
Well, you're gonna laugh.
I've been talking to
some people.

1325
01:39:57,358 --> 01:40:01,059
They think I may have given up
on the west too soon.

1326
01:40:01,128 --> 01:40:04,062
What could possibly
be out there for you?

1327
01:40:04,131 --> 01:40:06,131
San Francisco.

1328
01:40:07,535 --> 01:40:10,469
Come on!

1329
01:40:22,049 --> 01:40:24,717
So long, my friends!

1330
01:40:24,786 --> 01:40:28,387
Bye-bye!
Remember...

1331
01:40:28,456 --> 01:40:31,156
If you're ever
in my country again,

1332
01:40:31,225 --> 01:40:33,225
I'll have to kill you.

1333
01:40:33,294 --> 01:40:35,394
Ha ha ha!

1334
01:40:36,764 --> 01:40:40,232
I'm serious.

1335
01:40:52,580 --> 01:40:55,681
Wagons, ho!

